# Project Planning & Task Breakdown

## Milestones

- [ ] **M1**: All packages pass `pnpm build` + `pnpm type-check` + `pnpm lint`
- [ ] **M2**: Each package has tests, README, TypeDoc exports
- [ ] **M3**: Demo runs end-to-end without modification
- [ ] **M4**: npm packages published (`@trust402/identity`, `@trust402/roles`, `@trust402/protocol`)
- [ ] **M5**: Old x402-agent-privacy-pool docs archived

## Task Breakdown

### Phase 1: Audit & Triage

- [ ] **1.1** Audit each trust402 package for build/type-check/lint status
  - Run `pnpm --filter @trust402/identity build` and note errors
  - Run `pnpm --filter @trust402/roles build` and note errors
  - Run `pnpm --filter @trust402/protocol build` and note errors
  - Run `pnpm --filter @trust402/cli build` and note errors
  - Outcome: List of blocking issues per package

- [ ] **1.2** Audit test coverage per package
  - Run `pnpm --filter @trust402/protocol test` (only package with test command in package.json)
  - Outcome: Coverage report, missing tests identified

### Phase 2: Hardening

- [ ] **2.1** Fix build errors in @trust402/identity
  - Outcome: `pnpm --filter @trust402/identity build` succeeds

- [ ] **2.2** Fix build errors in @trust402/roles
  - Outcome: `pnpm --filter @trust402/roles build` succeeds

- [ ] **2.3** Fix build errors in @trust402/protocol
  - Outcome: `pnpm --filter @trust402/protocol build` succeeds

- [ ] **2.4** Fix build errors in @trust402/cli
  - Outcome: `pnpm --filter @trust402/cli build` succeeds

- [ ] **2.5** Add tests to packages missing them (@trust402/identity, @trust402/roles)
  - Outcome: Vitest tests for core logic

### Phase 3: Documentation & Publishing

- [ ] **3.1** Write README for @trust402/identity
  - Usage example, API reference, circuit ID, dependencies
  - Outcome: README.md in packages/identity/

- [ ] **3.2** Write README for @trust402/roles
  - Usage example, gate configuration, circuit ID
  - Outcome: README.md in packages/roles/

- [ ] **3.3** Write README for @trust402/protocol (may already exist)
  - `wrapFetchWithProof` usage, configuration options
  - Outcome: README.md in packages/protocol/

- [ ] **3.4** Verify demo runs end-to-end
  - `pnpm demo:resource` + `pnpm demo:agent` — both succeed
  - Outcome: Demo fully working

- [ ] **3.5** Publish packages to npm
  - Requires: npm account, publish access to @trust402 namespace
  - Outcome: `npm publish --access public` for each package

### Phase 4: Cleanup

- [ ] **4.1** Archive old x402-agent-privacy-pool docs
  - Delete or rename `docs/ai/requirements/2026-06-25-feature-x402-agent-privacy-pool.md`
  - Delete or rename `docs/ai/design/2026-06-25-feature-x402-agent-privacy-pool.md`
  - Delete or rename `docs/ai/planning/2026-06-25-feature-x402-agent-privacy-pool.md`
  - Outcome: Only trust402 SDK docs remain

- [ ] **4.2** Update trust402/CLAUDE.md if needed
  - Ensure it reflects SDK scope (not the killed privacy pool)

## Dependencies

```
1.1 (audit)
  │
  ├─► 2.1 (identity build)
  ├─► 2.2 (roles build)
  ├─► 2.3 (protocol build)
  └─► 2.4 (cli build)
            │
            ▼
      2.5 (add tests)
            │
            ▼
      3.1-3.4 (docs + demo)
            │
            ▼
      3.5 (npm publish)
            │
            ▼
      4.1-4.2 (cleanup)
```

## Timeline & Estimates

| Task | Estimate |
|------|----------|
| 1.1 Audit | 1h |
| 1.2 Test audit | 1h |
| 2.1 Fix identity build | 2h |
| 2.2 Fix roles build | 2h |
| 2.3 Fix protocol build | 2h |
| 2.4 Fix cli build | 2h |
| 2.5 Add tests | 4h |
| 3.1 Identity README | 1h |
| 3.2 Roles README | 1h |
| 3.3 Protocol README | 1h |
| 3.4 Demo verification | 2h |
| 3.5 npm publish | 1h |
| 4.1 Archive old docs | 1h |
| 4.2 Update CLAUDE.md | 1h |
| **Total** | **~22h** |

**Buffer**: +20% = **~26h** (3-4 days)

## Risks & Mitigation

| Risk | Likelihood | Impact | Mitigation |
|------|-----------|--------|------------|
| WASM proving fails in Node.js env | Low | Medium | Demo uses browser WASM; Node.js is stretch goal |
| @lemmaoracle/sdk breaks API | Low | High | Pin to specific version; mock in tests |
| npm namespace @trust402 taken | Low | High | Switch to @lemmaoracle scope |
| Demo requires x402 facilitator running | Medium | Medium | Document facilitator requirements in README |

## Resources Needed

- npm account with publish access to @trust402 namespace
- Base Sepolia USDC for demo (~$10 sufficient)
- x402 facilitator running (or documented mock flow)
- Node.js 18+ for local dev
